metadata.label: submit
metadata.description:
Submits an HTTP request to a service with the specified HTTP verb.
The `Client->submit()` function does not give out a `http:Response` as the result.
Rather it returns an `http:HttpFuture` which can be used to do further interactions with the endpoint.

metadata.label: Schema To JSON

metadata.label: Schema To XML
metadata.description:
Converts a `Map` or `Record` representation to its XML representation.
Additionally, when converting from a record, the `xmldata:Namespace`, `xmldata:Name`, and `xmldata:Attribute`
annotations can be used to add `namespaces`, `name of elements`, and `attributes` to XML representation.

metadata.label: XML To Schema

metadata.label: Evaluate JSON Path
metadata.description:
Extract details from the given JSON value using the provided query template expression.

```ballerina
read({id: 1, "name": "John Doe"}, `$.name`) => "John Doe"
```

metadata.label: JSON Pretty Print
metadata.description: Prettifies a `json` value to print it.

metadata.label: XSLT Transform
metadata.description:
Transforms the single-rooted XML content to another XML/HTML/plain text using XSL transformations.
```ballerina
xml|error target = xslt:transform(sourceXml, xsl);
```

metadata.description: This package provides a set of APIs that have the capabilities to generate and manipulate UTC and localized time.

metadata.description: Returns the UTC representing the current time.

metadata.description: Returns the number of seconds from an unspecified epoch.

metadata.label: Get Time Zone
metadata.description: Return the time zone object of a given zone ID.

metadata.label: Get Day of Week
metadata.description: Get the day of week for a specified date.

metadata.label: UTC Time Difference in Seconds
metadata.description: Returns the difference in seconds between `utc1` and `utc2`.

metadata.label: Add Seconds to UTC
metadata.description: Returns UTC time that occurs seconds after `utc`.

metadata.label: Validate Gregorian Date
metadata.description: Check that days and months are within range as per Gregorian calendar rules.

metadata.label: Convert Civil to UTC
